            procedure: `
                <h4 class="font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">Procedure:</h4>
                <ol class="list-decimal list-outside pl-5 space-y-2">
                    <li><strong>Loose:</strong> 100ml cylinder mein gently pour karein вҶ’ level off вҶ’ weigh.</li>
                    <li><strong>Tapped:</strong> Same cylinder ko 100 times tap karein вҶ’ new volume вҶ’ same mass.</li>
                </ol>

                <div class="bg-cyan-50 border border-cyan-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-cyan-800 mb-3">рҹ“җ FORMULAS:</h4>
                    <pre class="bg-white p-3 rounded border"><code>Loose Bulk Density (ПҒ_b) = Mass (g) / 100 (ml) = g/ml
Tapped Bulk Density (ПҒ_t) = Mass (g) / Tapped volume (ml) = g/ml

Carr Index = [(ПҒ_t - ПҒ_b) / ПҒ_t] Г— 100
  < 15% = Excellent flow
  15-25% = Good
  25-35% = Fair
  > 35% = Poor (needs vibration/fluidization)

Hausner Ratio = ПҒ_t / ПҒ_b
  < 1.20 = Free flowing
  > 1.40 = Poor

Example:
  Mass in 100ml = 48g (loose)
  After tapping, settles to 72ml
  ПҒ_b = 48/100 = 0.48 g/ml
  ПҒ_t = 48/72 = 0.667 g/ml
  Carr = [(0.667-0.48)/0.667] Г— 100 = 28% вҶ’ Fair
  Hausner = 0.667/0.48 = 1.39 вҶ’ Fair

Typical dairy whitener: 0.40-0.55 g/ml (loose)
  Instantized: 0.30-0.40 g/ml (more air = lighter)</code></pre>
                </div>
            `
